olive oil
½ lemon
2 packet diced bacon
1 drizzle balsamic vinegar
½ tsp honey
½ packet panko breadcrumbs
1 packet spaghetti
1 sachet Garlic & Herb Seasoning
½ bottle cream
1 bag Mixed Salad Leaves
1 tomato
1 packet Grated Parmesan Cheese

• Boil the kettle. Zest lemon to get a good pinch and slice into wedges. Thinly slice tomato.
• Half-fill a large saucepan with boiling water, add a generous pinch of salt, then bring to the boil over high heat.
• Cook spaghetti, uncovered, until 'al dente', 10 minutes. Reserve some pasta water (1/2 cup for 2 people / 1 cup for 4 people).

Little cooks: Older kids can help add the pasta to the saucepan under adult supervision. Be careful, the water is boiling!

• Heat a large frying pan to medium heat with a good drizzle of olive oil. Toast panko breadcrumbs (see ingredients), stirring, until golden brown, 3 minutes.
• Add lemon zest and cook until fragrant, 1-2 minutes. Transfer to a medium bowl, season with a pinch of salt and pepper and set aside.

• Return frying pan to medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Cook diced bacon, breaking up with a spoon, until golden, 7-9 minutes.
• Reduce heat to medium, add garlic & herb seasoning, cream (see ingredients) and the reserved pasta water (1/4 cup for 2 people / 1/2 cup for 4 people). Cook until slightly thickened, 2-3 minutes.
• Remove pan from heat and gently stir through spaghetti, grated Parmesan cheese and a squeeze of lemon juice. Season with salt and pepper.

TIP: Add a splash of pasta water if the sauce looks too thick.

• In a medium bowl, combine a drizzle of balsamic vinegar, olive oil and the honey. Add mixed salad leaves and tomato and toss to combine.
• Divide creamy bacon spaghetti between bowls. Top with the lemon pangrattato. Serve with tomato salad and any remaining lemon wedges. Enjoy!